HOUSE RESOLUTION NO. 164
BY REPRESENTATIVE LYONS
A RESOLUTION
To commend Flau'jae Johnson for her accomplishments at Louisiana State University.
WHEREAS, it is most fitting to recognize Flau'jae Johnson for her outstanding
achievements in athletics, leadership, and community service at Louisiana State University;
and
WHEREAS, Flau'jae Johnson enrolled at Louisiana State University in 2022 as an
exceptional student-athlete and has since emerged as one of the most accomplished
collegiate athletes in the nation; and
WHEREAS, as a freshman member of the LSU women's basketball team, Flau'jae
played a vital role in leading the team to victory in the 2023 NCAA National Championship,
contributing significantly as a starter on a historic championship roster; and
WHEREAS, throughout her collegiate career, Flau'jae has earned numerous
individual honors, including Southeastern Conference Freshman of the Year, multiple
All-Southeastern Conference selections, and multiple All-American recognitions,
culminating in her selection to the prestigious John R. Wooden All-America Team; and
WHEREAS, Flau'jae has further distinguished herself by representing the United
States in international competition, earning a gold medal as a member of Team USA in the
FIBA Women's AmeriCup; and
WHEREAS, beyond her accomplishments on the court, Flau'jae has demonstrated
exemplary leadership and service, earning national recognition as the recipient of the Kay
Yow Servant Leader Award, which honors student-athletes who exemplify compassion,
advocacy, and a commitment to community service; and
