WHEREAS, Flau'jae's advocacy efforts, particularly in raising awareness for cancer
research and her engagement with youth and community initiatives, have made a meaningful
and lasting impact across Louisiana and beyond; and
WHEREAS, Flau'jae has excelled academically as a student in the LSU Honors
College, pursuing a degree in nursing while maintaining a 4.0 grade point average,
demonstrating discipline and commitment to academic excellence; and
WHEREAS, in addition to her achievements in athletics and academics, Flau'jae has
used her platform as both a nationally recognized athlete and recording artist to inspire
young people and promote positive community engagement; and
WHEREAS, Flau'jae has positioned herself as a leading figure in collegiate athletics
through name, image, and likeness opportunities while maintaining a strong commitment to
integrity, responsibility, and service; and
WHEREAS, Flau'jae Johnson is an outstanding student-athlete and community
servant who has brought great pride to Louisiana State University and the state of Louisiana,
and she is deserving of the highest recognition for her many achievements.
THEREFORE, BE IT RESOLVED that the House of Representatives of the
Legislature of Louisiana does hereby commend Flau'jae Johnson for her outstanding
achievements in athletics, academics, leadership, and community service at Louisiana State
University and does hereby extend sincere wishes for continued success and happiness in
all of her endeavors.
SPEAKER OF THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
